Gulf Stocks: Abu Dhabi’s Aldar Properties and Dubai’s Depa

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-03-07T11:56:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/gulf-stocks-abu-dhabi-s-aldar-properties-and-dubai-s-depa.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  slipped 1
percent, the most since March 3, at the 2 p.m. close in the
emirate. The  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  lost 0.4 percent.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Gulf. Symbols are
in parentheses.        Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR)   decreased the most since
March 2, dropping 3.8 percent to 1.27 dirhams. Abu Dhabi’s
biggest developer said its 2.8 billion dirhams ($762 million) of
convertible bonds will pay an interest rate of 4 percent a year.
The securities will be sold to Mubadala Development Co.    Depa Ltd. (DEPA)   dropped to the lowest level since
October, retreating 2.9 percent to $0.64. The interior design
contractor that fitted out the world’s tallest tower in Dubai
said 2010 profit will be “significantly impacted” due a claim
related to the Burj Khalifa contract.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  